Not sure if I understand this correctly but.

I think its "fine" that they don't do backward compatibility for 4000 series with older mobos. Since (some)b350 - x470 can support the 3000 series chips which are CRAZY GOOD. Although I just hope at least with the 4000 series chips, they **could** still be compatible with (some)b450 and (most)x470, of course depending on the mobos. After that, chips onwards are strictly on the new AM5 motherboards. But I guess they can't control that.. if it doesn't work then it doesn't work :'(

If I'm wrong I would highly suggest someone to correct me, I would like to know more about the compatibility with the boards!
